%%time

news = df.copy()

analyzer = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()

sentiment_vader = pd.DataFrame()
sentiment_vader['vader'] = news['clean_lem_text'].parallel_apply(analyzer.polarity_scores)
sentiment_vader = pd.DataFrame(sentiment_vader['vader'].tolist())

# Create a positive / negative sentiment variable
sentiment_vader['sentiment'] = np.where(sentiment_vader['compound'].astype(float) > 0, 'Positive', 'Negative')
sentiment_vader['sentiment'] = np.where(sentiment_vader['compound'].astype(float) == 0, 'Neutral', sentiment_vader['sentiment'])

%%time

# Load the SpaCy NER model
nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_sm")

# Define a function to extract industry-related named entities
def extract_industry_entities(text):
    doc = nlp(text
    industry_entities = [entity.text for entity in doc.ents if entity.label_ == "ORG"]
    return industry_entities

# Apply the function to each sentiment DataFrame
positive_sentiments['industry_entities'] = positive_sentiments['clean_lem_text'].parallel_apply(extract_industry_entities)
negative_sentiments['industry_entities'] = negative_sentiments['clean_lem_text'].parallel_apply(extract_industry_entities)
neutral_sentiments['industry_entities'] = neutral_sentiments['clean_lem_text'].parallel_apply(extract_industry_entities)

# Function to print most common entities in a DataFrame
def print_most_common_entities(df, sentiment_label):
    all_industry_entities = df['industry_entities'].sum()
    industry_entity_counts = Counter(all_industry_entities)
    
    print(f"Most common industry entities in {sentiment_label} sentiment:")
    for entity, count in industry_entity_counts.most_common(20):
        print(f"{entity}: {count}")

# Extract and format month and year
news_senti['Month_Year'] = news_senti['date'].dt.strftime('%b %Y')

# Convert 'Month_Year' column to datetime format
news_senti['Month_Year'] = pd.to_datetime(news_senti['Month_Year'])

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

# Count the number of articles per month-year
monthly_counts = news_senti['Month_Year'].value_counts()

# Sort the index (datetime values) in chronological order
monthly_counts = monthly_counts.sort_index()

# Create the bar plot using Seaborn
ax = sns.barplot(x=monthly_counts.index, y=monthly_counts.values, color='blue')

plt.xlabel('Month Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Articles')
plt.title('Monthly Distribution of Articles Over Time')

# Reformat the x-axis labels to 'Jan 2020' format
ax.set_xticklabels(monthly_counts.index.strftime('%b %Y'), rotation=90)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
